{
  "stem": "19218.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And how can you get your shoes?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody's running for their shoes so you pick anything that you could-- that you could wear.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and-- and they-- I remember this was, God February-- February.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Could have been February 1, February 2.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I have-- I have chosen the day of observance-- in our language it's called yahrzeit-- for my parents.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I believe we have arrived at February 2 or so into-- or January 31.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I honestly do not recall the exact date.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I have chosen February 2 as the memorial day for my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I figured they probably couldn't kill everybody the same night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I learned otherwise later on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But anyway, so I have chosen February 2 as the observance day for my yahrzeit, which corresponds to the Jewish calendar 27 days in Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had to call here-- when I came to this country finally, I called a rabbi in here who established the date for me to correspond to February 2, what the Jewish date would be.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this is my observance in there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We spent-- I spent probably about five to six weeks in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They called it actually the quarantine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whoever died-- many people died in Birkenau, many of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the-- the people that I would say the wealthier, who had it good and had maids in the house and didn't do any physical work during their lifetime, they were the first ones to die.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My brother-in-law's brother died in my arms in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, we weren't working even yet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Of course, they didn't give us much food, either.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But many of these people, of our people, died days after they have arrived.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
